Load model and dataset¶

In [ ]:
if torch.cuda.is_available():
    device = 'cuda:0'
else:
    device = 'cpu'

# load dataset
name = 'TSP'
keig = 0
trainset = GNNBenchmarkDataset(root=name, name=name, split='train')
testset = GNNBenchmarkDataset(root=name, name=name, split='test')
trainset1 = TSP_EigPE(root=osp.join(name,'train_data'), dataset=trainset, keig=keig+1)
testset1 = TSP_EigPE(root=osp.join(name,'test_data'), dataset=testset, keig=keig+1)
train_loader = DataLoader(trainset1, batch_size=1, shuffle=False, num_workers=4)
test_loader = DataLoader(testset1, batch_size=1, num_workers=4)

# load model
fold = 3
model = HL_HGCNN(channels=[4,4,4], filters=[64,128,256], mlp_channels=[], K=4, dropout_ratio=0.25, 
                  dropout_ratio_mlp=0.0, keig=keig).to(device)
save_path = './selected_model_para/HGCNN_dense_int3_eigpe10_pyr_focal_aug75_TSP_444conv_k4_mlp0_FOLD{}.pt'.format(fold)
model.load_state_dict(torch.load(save_path))

datax = Data(x=data.x_t, edge_index=data.edge_index, edge_attr=data.x_s[:,0])
netdata = to_networkx(data.detach().cpu(),to_undirected=True)
node_size = 50

Input graph signal¶

In [ ]:
plt.clf()
pos_n = {i:datax.cpu().x[i,:2].numpy() for i in range(data.x_t.shape[0])}
edge_c = data.x_s[:,0].cpu().numpy()
node_c = data.x_t[:,:2].mean(dim=1).view(-1).cpu().numpy()
temp = nx.draw_networkx(netdata, pos=pos_n, with_labels=False, node_size=node_size,
                        edge_vmin=0,edge_vmax=edge_c.max(),
                 edge_color=edge_c, edge_cmap=plt.cm.Reds,vmin=0,vmax=1,
                       cmap=plt.cm.Greys,node_color=node_c,width=0.5)
